                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/639: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-19T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 19—6:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>819. Legation’s 765, July 27, 6 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Cunningham has requested, August 17, 3 p.m., instructions “to protest
                        individually against all the September 1st taxes,” stating his belief that
                        such protest would have a salutary effect upon the Chinese authorities. I
                        request the Department’s approval of the foregoing.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I am replying as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“I assume that the September 1st taxes to which you refer, are those
                                described in your 97, July 26 [<hi rend="italic">27?</hi>], 9 a.m.
                                If you consider that a protest against these taxes would have a
                                salutary effect upon the Chinese authorities you may, at your
                                discretion, make such a protest either individually or jointly with
                                your colleagues.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
